#. <section class="sutta" id="sn55.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Sagāthakapuññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "5. Overflowing Merit, With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 43. Tatiyaabhisandasutta → tatiyaasaṅkheyyasuttaṃ (bj) | abhisanda or sayhaka 3 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn55.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Tatiyaabhisandasutta"
msgstr "43. Overflowing Merit (3rd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.43:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puññābhisandā, kusalābhisandā, sukhassāhārā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing "
"goodness that nurture happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha …"

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn55.43:1.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ paṭhamo puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.43:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako dhamme … pe …"
msgstr "the teaching …"

msgctxt "sn55.43:2.2"
msgid "saṅghe … pe …."
msgstr "the Saṅgha …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.402"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.43:3.1"
msgid ""
"Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya "
"samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"Furthermore, a mendicant is wise. They have the wisdom of arising and "
"passing away which is noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending "
"of suffering."

msgctxt "sn55.43:3.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ catuttho puññābhisando kusalābhisando sukhassāhāro."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth kind of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurtures happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.43:3.3"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puññābhisandā kusalābhisandā sukhassāhārā."
msgstr ""
"These are the four kinds of overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurture happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.43:4.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, catūhi puññābhisandehi kusalābhisandehi samannāgatassa "
"ariyasāvakassa na sukaraṃ puññassa pamāṇaṃ gaṇetuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple has these four kinds of overflowing merit and "
"goodness, it’s not easy to measure how much merit they have by saying that"

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.2"
msgid "‘ettako puññābhisando, kusalābhisando, sukhassāhāro’ti."
msgstr ""
"this is the extent of their overflowing merit, overflowing goodness that "
"nurtures happiness."

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho asaṅkhyeyyo appameyyo mahāpuññakkhandhotveva saṅkhyaṃ gacchatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s simply reckoned as an incalculable, immeasurable, great mass of merit.”"

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn55.43:4.5"
msgid "satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.1"
msgid "“Yo puññakāmo kusale patiṭṭhito,"
msgstr "“One who desires merit, grounded in the skillful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.2"
msgid "Bhāveti maggaṃ amatassa pattiyā;"
msgstr "develops the eight-fold path for realizing the deathless."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.3"
msgid "So dhammasārādhigamo khaye rato,"
msgstr "Once they’ve reached the heart of the teaching, delighting in ending,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: maccurājāgamanasmin”ti → maccurājā gamissatīti (bj) | maccurājāgamasminti (s1-3) | maccurāja gamissatīti (pts1) | maccujarākampisminti (mr)
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.4"
msgid "Na vedhati maccurājāgamanasmin”ti."
msgstr "they don’t tremble at the approach of the King of Death.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.43:5.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
